verbose_text: Phosphatase, orphan 1 (PHOSPHO1) is another essential phosphatase, located within osteoblast- and chondrocyte derived MVs with high phosphohydrolase activity toward phosphoethanolamine and phosphocholine, which contributes Pi for the initiation of skeletal mineralisation.
